align: left;\">50\u00b0C\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 5min<\/p>\n<p>95\u00b0C\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 2min<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>95\u00b0C\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 3s\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 40X<\/p>\n<p>60\u00b0C\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 30s*<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>\u00a0*Data aquisition step<\/p>"},"is_project":0},{"component_id":"1075270","previous_id":"1075269","original_id":"0","guid":"D3A89A4743F445BA9CE645F4D537D967","previous_guid":"672393239BED448DBCBEAC665A4F71AA","component_type_id":"6","data_id":"0","data":"AMPLIFICATION","order_id":"1","name":"Section","data_by_id":"0","type_id":"6","source_data":{"section":"AMPLIFICATION"},"is_project":0}],"available_protocols":["11031"]},{"id":"616256","is_changed":1,"original_id":"0","is_skipped":"0","is_checked":"0","guid":"CFE116F6B1C04AC0B291DE4162DE0C65","previous_guid":"4BF3F053F6FE499CA8A8BFCC3E211B0E","previous_id":"615838","last_modified":"1521765928","components":[{"component_id":"1076402","previous_id":0,"original_id":"0","guid":"5AA84645A9F04471A24E2665CCA5BF55","previous_guid":null,"component_type_id":"1","data_id":null,"data":"<p>Assay has been used on both a Rotor-Gene 6000 \/ Rotor-Gene Q 5-plex using 100-place rotor discs.<\/p>\n<p>Total reaction volume is 20\u00b5L.<\/p>\n<p>Prepare sufficient for number of reaction plus a 'dead volume' usually 2 extra. Adjust as necessary if using a robotic dispenser.<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<table style=\"width: 538px; background-color: #f9f3ed; border-color: #e9967a; height: 180px;\" border=\"#e9967a\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">Reagent<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">Volume (uL)<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">Final concentration<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">Nuclease-free water<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">4.87<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">\u00a0<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">SensiFast Probe Lo-Rox mix<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">10<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">1X<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">OPV2018-F<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">0.05<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">500nM<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">OPV2018-R<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">0.05<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">500nM<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">OPV2018-FAM<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">0.03<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">150nM<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\"><strong>TOTAL VOLUME<\/strong><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\"><strong>15<\/strong><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">\u00a0<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>","order_id":"0","name":"Description","data_by_id":"0","type_id":"1","source_data":{"description":"<p>Assay has been used on both a Rotor-Gene 6000 \/ Rotor-Gene Q 5-plex using 100-place rotor discs.<\/p>\n<p>Total reaction volume is 20\u00b5L.<\/p>\n<p>Prepare sufficient for number of reaction plus a 'dead volume' usually 2 extra. Adjust as necessary if using a robotic dispenser.<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<table style=\"width: 538px; background-color: #f9f3ed; border-color: #e9967a; height: 180px;\" border=\"#e9967a\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">Reagent<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">Volume (uL)<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">Final concentration<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">Nuclease-free water<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">4.87<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">\u00a0<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">SensiFast Probe Lo-Rox mix<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">10<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">1X<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">OPV2018-F<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">0.05<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">500nM<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">OPV2018-R<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">0.05<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">500nM<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\">OPV2018-FAM<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\">0.03<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">150nM<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 205.45px;\"><strong>TOTAL VOLUME<\/strong><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 112.817px;\"><strong>15<\/strong><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 197.733px;\">\u00a0<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>"},"is_project":0},{"component_id":"1076403","previous_id":"1076402","original_id":"0","guid":"692953802A7E421C9169F59F4AF00C6C","previous_guid":"5AA84645A9F04471A24E2665CCA5BF55","component_type_id":"6","data_id":"0","data":"REACTION SET-UP","order_id":"1","name":"Section","data_by_id":"0","type_id":"6","source_data":{"section":"REACTION SET-UP"},"is_project":0}],"available_protocols":["11031"]},{"id":"616257","is_changed":"0","original_id":"0","is_skipped":"0","is_checked":"0","guid":"DF4BC700B3E5482E93B6A0AB0EBF6F1A","previous_guid":"E643D04F8DE549AF831D5CB95AEAD461","previous_id":"615839","last_modified":"1521765975","components":[{"component_id":"1076408","previous_id":0,"original_id":"0","guid":"29753067565A4F51A775FD248DC3EA66","previous_guid":null,"component_type_id":"6","data_id":"0","data":"RESULT ANALYSIS","order_id":"0","name":"Section","data_by_id":"0","type_id":"6","source_data":{"section":"RESULT ANALYSIS"},"is_project":0},{"component_id":"1076407","previous_id":"1076408","original_id":"0","guid":"96AD9F86930E455EA9515A234575318A","previous_guid":"29753067565A4F51A775FD248DC3EA66","component_type_id":"1","data_id":null,"data":"<p>The definition used for a satisfactory positive result from a real-time fluorogenic PCR should include each of the following:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>A\u00a0<strong>sigmoidal curve<\/strong>\u00a0\u2013 the trace travels horizontally, curves upward, continues in an exponential rise and followed by a curve towards a horizontal plateau phase<\/li>\n<li>A\u00a0<strong>suitable level of fluorescence<\/strong>\u00a0intensity as measured in comparison to a positive control (y-axis)<\/li>\n<li>A defined threshold (C<sub>T<\/sub>) value which the fluorescent curve has clearly exceeded (Fig.1 arrow) and which sits early in the log-linear phase and is &lt;40 cycles<\/li>\n<li>A flat or non-sigmoidal curve or a curve that crosses the threshold with a C<sub>T<\/sub>\u00a0value &gt;40 cycles is considered a negative result<\/li>\n<li>NTCs should not produce a curve<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><img id=\"s-mce-img\" class=\"s-mce-img\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/u3ghz4w.png\" data-src=\"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/u3ghz4w.png\" data-ofn=\"TaqMan curves.png\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>Figure 1<\/strong>. Examples of satisfactory sigmoidal amplification curve shape when considering an assay\u2019s fluorescent signal output. The crossing point or threshold cycle (C<sub>T<\/sub>) is indicated (yellow arrow); it is the value at which fluorescence levels surpass a predefined (usually set during validation, or arbitrary) threshold level as shown in this normalized linear scale depiction. LP-log-linear phase of signal generated during the exponential part of the PCR amplification; TP-a slowing of the amplification and accompanying fluorescence signal marks the transition phase; PP-the plateau phase is reached when there is little or no increase in fluorescent signal despite continued cycling.<\/p>","order_id":"1","name":"Description","data_by_id":"0","type_id":"1","source_data":{"description":"<p>The definition used for a satisfactory positive result from a real-time fluorogenic PCR should include each of the following:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>A\u00a0<strong>sigmoidal curve<\/strong>\u00a0\u2013 the trace travels horizontally, curves upward, continues in an exponential rise and followed by a curve towards a horizontal plateau phase<\/li>\n<li>A\u00a0<strong>suitable level of fluorescence<\/strong>\u00a0intensity as measured in comparison to a positive control (y-axis)<\/li>\n<li>A defined threshold (C<sub>T<\/sub>) value which the fluorescent curve has clearly exceeded (Fig.1 arrow) and which sits early in the log-linear phase and is &lt;40 cycles<\/li>\n<li>A flat or non-sigmoidal curve or a curve that crosses the threshold with a C<sub>T<\/sub>\u00a0value &gt;40 cycles is considered a negative result<\/li>\n<li>NTCs should not produce a curve<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><img id=\"s-mce-img\" class=\"s-mce-img\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/u3ghz4w.png\" data-src=\"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/u3ghz4w.png\" data-ofn=\"TaqMan curves.png\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>Figure 1<\/strong>. Examples of satisfactory sigmoidal amplification curve shape when considering an assay\u2019s fluorescent signal output. The crossing point or threshold cycle (C<sub>T<\/sub>) is indicated (yellow arrow); it is the value at which fluorescence levels surpass a predefined (usually set during validation, or arbitrary) threshold level as shown in this normalized linear scale depiction. LP-log-linear phase of signal generated during the exponential part of the PCR amplification; TP-a slowing of the amplification and accompanying fluorescence signal marks the transition phase; PP-the plateau phase is reached when there is little or no increase in fluorescent signal despite continued cycling.<\/p>"},"is_project":0}]}]}